689. Acherunti. See note on v. 998. clueas. Like Gk. κλύω, ‘to be spoken of,' ‘to be celebrated’ (cf. κλυτός, inclutus), was O. Lat. clueo, common in Plautus and other Republican poets. Its intransitive use accounts for its presence in the Second Conjugation in Latin, the Con- jugation appropriate to Intransitives (cf. pendeo Intrans. beside pendo Trans„ and see note on intueor, V. 557>; also for its occasional Deponent form, eg.
